==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[house]] [[number]]}}

# The single [[object]] or multiple objects attached to a [[building]] to [[display]] the [[street address]] [[assigned]] to that [[structure]].  House numbers typically come as thin strips of [[metal]] with individual [[digit]]s printed on them, pre-applied with [[adhesive]] at the [[factory]] by the [[manufacturer]] to allow the [[purchaser]] to [[affix]] the numbers to the front or side of the structure, or as [[solid]] pieces of metal in the [[shape]] of the [[number]] and are [[secured]] to the structure with [[fastener]]s such as [[screw]]s.  There are also other types for decorative purposes such as [[carve]]d or [[engrave]]d into [[brick]], [[wood]] or [[stone]], etc.  Note that the [[device]]s used to [[affix]] an address on a structure is called a "house number" even if it is attached to a [[commercial]] building rather than actually on a house.

